# Performance & Speed Optimization

- Implement dynamic imports and code splitting for all heavy components and libraries
- Use Next.js Image component with WebP and AVIF formats, lazy loading, and proper sizing
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size by analyzing with `@next/bundle-analyzer`
- Implement React Server Components wherever possible to reduce client-side JavaScript
- Use streaming SSR with Suspense boundaries for faster Time to First Byte
- Preload critical fonts using `next/font` with `font-display: swap`
- Implement HTTP/2 server push for critical CSS and JavaScript files
- Use a CDN for static assets with proper cache headers (Cache-Control, ETag)
- Minimize third-party scripts and load them asynchronously or defer when possible
- Implement resource hints like preconnect, prefetch, and dns-prefetch for external domains
- Compress responses with Brotli or Gzip
- Remove unused CSS with PurgeCSS or built-in Tailwind purging
- Implement service workers for offline functionality and faster repeat visits
- Use React.memo, useMemo, and useCallback to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Implement virtual scrolling for long product lists using react-window or react-virtualized
- Optimize Core Web Vitals  
  - LCP < 2.5s  
  - FID < 100ms  
  - CLS < 0.1
- Use edge functions for geographically distributed API responses
- Implement database connection pooling to reduce query latency
- Use Redis or similar caching layer for frequently accessed data
- Optimize database queries with proper indexing and avoid N+1 problems

