# Responsive Design & Cross-Device Compatibility

- Follow a mobile-first CSS approach using min-width media queries
- Use breakpoints  
  - Mobile: 320–767px  
  - Tablet: 768–1023px  
  - Laptop: 1024–1439px  
  - Desktop: 1440px+
- Test on real devices, not just DevTools
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for adaptive layouts
- Ensure touch targets are at least 44x44px
- Optimize mobile navigation with hamburger or bottom nav
- Use responsive images with srcset and sizes
- Implement fluid typography with rem, em, or clamp
- Optimize form inputs for mobile keyboards
- Support swipe gestures for carousels
- Avoid hover-only interactions on touch devices
- Test both landscape and portrait orientations
- Optimize mobile checkout flows
- Use sticky headers carefully on mobile
- Maintain minimum 16px font size on mobile
- Test across Chrome, Safari, Firefox, and Edge
- Use correct viewport meta tag
- Ensure responsive videos
- Account for safe areas on devices with notches
- Implement responsive tables that stack or scroll
